{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 1186470, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Liffers", "body": "Muradin currently doesn't have a very good attention span. At current patch he stands facing the corner of his throne rather than looking outward from it like Moira and Falstad.\r\n\r\nMaybe his brain is still a little scattered from loosing his memory?", "date": "2010-11-26T01:44:21-06:00", "rating": 28, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "My first impression was that he was intentionally facing away from Moira, a little dis to the Dark Iron's. Or on a more personal note a dis to his niece and her son ( half Bronzebeard, half Thaurissan. )", "creationdate": "2010-12-02T14:27:07-06:00", "id": 198209, "rating": 12, "commentid": 1186470, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "archorian", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This is what I was guessing too. But his angle is just...off? It's like he should be 180 degrees from Moira, or 180 from his throne.", "creationdate": "2010-12-17T06:03:28-06:00", "id": 204820, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1186470, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "242284", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 1215116, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "722880", "body": "I love how he says the line: \"Welcome to our home beneath the mountain!\"\r\nOne of my favorite characters.", "date": "2010-12-08T13:56:52-06:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Has anyone digged out his sound scripts yet?  EDIT: Nevermind i got them:  Greeting 1: Muradin of clan Bronzebeard, at your service. [code]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Muradin\\\\VO_IF_Muradin_Greeting01.wav\")[/code]  Greeting 2: How can the Council of Three Hammers assist ye? [code]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Muradin\\\\VO_IF_Muradin_Greeting02.wav\")[/code]  Greeting 3: Welcome to our home beneath the mountain. [code]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Muradin\\\\VO_IF_Muradin_Greeting03.wav\")[/code]  Greeting 4: What brings ye to Ironforge friend? [code]/script PlaySound", "creationdate": "2010-12-08T13:56:53-06:00", "id": 484864, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1215116, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "WyvernVJ", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 1241937, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Stonehearth", "body": "Muradin uses the same abilities as King Magni Bronzebeard did (R.I.P):\r\n\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=19135]Avatar[/url][/li]\r\n[li][url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=84831]Stormbolt[/url][/li]\r\n[li][url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=20686]Knock Away[/url][/li]\r\n[/ul]", "date": "2010-12-17T23:16:56-06:00", "rating": 18, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "True. Also Avatar and Stormbolt are originally of Muradin's from WCIII, while I guess Knock Away is a developed concept of Bash, the passive ability of Muradin. Blizzard probably didn't want to give Magni a new set of abilities because there were no Muradin in game to Stormbolt, Bash, and Avatar.", "creationdate": "2014-12-25T18:21:25-06:00", "id": 818526, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1241937, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kathe", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Magni is petrified in diamond. Perfectly preserved. Yup, they had a funeral and even the Horde sent representatives. But all that doesn't necessarily mean he is dead. Dagran Thaurissan was merely a set back. He WILL be back for Dagran Thaurissan II. God help us if he isn't.", "creationdate": "2015-10-06T04:27:17-05:00", "id": 903023, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1241937, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Taraezor", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "And in Legion Magni is back, saw that for the first time since Anvilmar there is peace among the dwarf clans and opted to not resume the throne as was his right.", "creationdate": "2017-11-02T10:44:42-05:00", "id": 1082680, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1241937, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "KenjiT28", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
